<TITLE> Outgoing NBR chairman seeks to retire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, October 22 (bdnews24.com) -- Outgoing NBR chairman Badiur Rahman Monday said he had sought voluntary retirement from public services. "I have failed to please my master," Rahman told reporters at the National Board of Revenue. Rahman who was appointed as the country's chief revenue collector on Jan 21 was transferred in a major administrative reshuffle on October 18. The same day, he applied for voluntary retirement. "The government should consult secretaries before transfer," he said in Monday's press briefing. Rahman, secretary of the Internal Resources Division and chairman of the NBR, was transferred to the food and disaster management ministry. Mohammad Abdul Majid, member of the Planning Commission, became NBR chairman. bdn
